<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>📦 WD001 Week 3 — English Worksheet</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> The Box Model — Padding, Margin, Border · <strong>Course:</strong> Web Design: CSS · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes</p>
<p>This week you learn that <strong>every element is a box</strong>. Around the content there is <code>padding</code> (space <strong>inside</strong> the box), then a <code>border</code> (the line <strong>around</strong> it), then <code>margin</code> (space <strong>outside</strong>, pushing other boxes away). You will also use <code>border-radius</code> to round the corners.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each bit of CSS. Before you imagine the browser drawing it, write what you think will happen.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;style&gt;
  .card {
    border: 2px solid red;
    padding: 30px;
  }
&lt;/style&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Lots of padding. Is the text close to the border or far from it?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;style&gt;
  .card {
    border: 2px solid black;
    margin: 40px;
  }
&lt;/style&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Lots of margin. Does the space go </strong>inside<strong> the box or </strong>outside<strong> it, pushing other things away?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;style&gt;
  .card {
    border-radius: 50px;
    width: 100px;
    height: 100px;
  }
&lt;/style&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>A 100×100 box with a 50px corner radius. What shape do you think it becomes?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;style&gt;
  .card {
    padding: 0px;
    border: 1px solid blue;
  }
&lt;/style&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>No padding at all. Where does the text sit compared to the border line?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Each bit of CSS below was meant to do something, but it is broken. Read what it is <strong>supposed</strong> to do, then rewrite it so it works. After that, explain why the original was wrong and why your fix works.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — The card is supposed to have a visible line around it. There is no line.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;style&gt;
  .card {
    border: solid blue;
  }
&lt;/style&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> a border needs a <strong>thickness</strong> too.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — The text inside the card is supposed to have breathing room, but it is squished right up against the border.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;style&gt;
  .card {
    border: 2px solid green;
    margin: 20px;
  }
&lt;/style&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> which property adds space <strong>inside</strong> the box?</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — The card is supposed to have softly rounded corners, but the corners are still sharp.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;style&gt;
  .card {
    border: 2px solid #d4380d;
    radius: 12px;
  }
&lt;/style&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> check the property name.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Build 3 Cards 📸</h2>
<p>In Replit, build <strong>3 cards</strong> about you — for example: favourite food, favourite movie, favourite school subject. Each card has a heading and a short line of text. Make each card a little <strong>different</strong> in colour or border so they don't all look the same.</p>
<p>You can start one card like this and change it to your own:</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;div class=&quot;card&quot;&gt;
  &lt;h2&gt;My Favorite Game&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Minecraft is the best!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;style&gt;
  .card {
    background-color: #ffffff;
    border: 2px solid #d4380d;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 20px;
    margin: 16px;
    width: 300px;
  }
&lt;/style&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>When you finish, send a <strong>photo or video</strong> of your cards (or a picture of your code), then explain what you did. Use these sentence starters — write 4 to 6 sentences total.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My three cards are about …</p>
<p>I made them look different by …</p>
<p>I used padding to …</p>
<p>I used border-radius to …</p>
<p>One tricky moment was when …</p>
<p>If I had more time, I would …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Now take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) while you show your cards. Talk through it like you are teaching someone who has never seen the box model. Try to use these words: <strong>box</strong>, <strong>padding</strong>, <strong>margin</strong>, <strong>border</strong>, <strong>rounded</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your three cards in the browser.</li>
<li>Point to one card and show where the padding is and where the margin is.</li>
<li>Say what <code>border-radius</code> did to the corners.</li>
<li>Show one thing you got wrong at first and how you fixed it.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> Use the space below to plan it before you record — you can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
